The paper proposes a data augmentation method using a conditional generative adversarial network (CGAN) for time series with irregular sampling. This involves using neural networks for both the generative and discriminative steps, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions using convolutional and deconvolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses evaluating the method on synthetic and real-world datasets, which suggests a focus on neural networks for classification (cs.NE).
